# Lead Quanta Workflows

Critical workflow details for build. See **platform-personas** for permissions and journeys.

## End-to-end system features

| Feature | Trigger | Journey | System output | Primary owner |
|---------|---------|---------|---------------|---------------|
| **Manual valuation** | Periodic or event-driven valuation input | Capture valuation input and supporting evidence. Reviewer approves input where needed. | Updated valuation record with audit trail | Valuation reviewer (Risk / Finance) |
| **Maturity, sale and rollover** | Maturity alert, sale decision, or rollover instruction | Notify users. Trader raises maturity action, sale slip, or rollover deal slip. Approvals and settlement follow normal workflow. | Closed, matured, sold, partially sold, or rolled over position; new deal slip where applicable | Trader, Back Office, Finance |
| **Limits and compliance monitoring** | Pre-trade, post-trade, daily batch, or portfolio change | Measure exposure by counterparty, issuer, group, rating, asset class, sector, currency, fund, regulatory rule. Route breaches. | Within limit, watch level, breach, override approved, or remediation pending | Middle Office, Risk, Compliance |
| **Accounting and GL interface** | Settlement confirmed, accrual run, valuation run, maturity, or disposal | Finance validates classification and journal output. System exports posting file to ERP/GL. Reconcile subledger to ledger. | Posted journal file, reconciliation report, exception list | Finance |
| **Dashboards and reports** | Daily cycle, period end, or committee reporting | Aggregate blotter, register, maturities, income, performance, exposure, limits, exceptions, accounting status. | Trader dashboard, PM dashboard, Head of Investments dashboard, ALCO pack | System |
| **Audit trail and user administration** | Any user or system action | Record user, action, timestamp, old/new value, approval step, documents, reason. Admin maintains roles and workflows. | Audit log, access log, workflow configuration, evidence pack | System Admin, Internal Audit |

## 6.1 Deal slip status flow

Implement as a state machine. Enforce system rules at each transition.

| Status | Meaning | System rule |
|--------|---------|-------------|
| **Draft** | Trader preparing deal slip | Trader can edit. Reviewers cannot approve. |
| **Submitted** | Submitted for review | Record locked except via returned-amendment workflow. |
| **Under Review** | Middle Office, Risk, or Compliance reviewing | Capture comments, queries, clearance. |
| **Returned for Amendment** | Correction or missing evidence required | Trader edits and resubmits. Prior version stays in audit log. |
| **Rejected** | Trade not approved | No settlement instruction can be created. |
| **Approved** | Approver approved the deal | Back Office settlement queue entry created. |
| **Pending Settlement** | Settlement instruction and payment validation in progress | Cannot become active investment yet. |
| **Settled** | Cash, documents, confirmations match approved deal slip | Investment register update triggered. |
| **Active** | Position in investment register | Accrual, valuation, maturity, limit monitoring run. |
| **Matured, Sold or Rolled Over** | Lifecycle event closed or transformed holding | Income, principal, register status updated. |

### Status transition summary

```
Draft → Submitted → Under Review → Approved → Pending Settlement → Settled → Active
                      ↓              ↓
              Returned for Amendment  Rejected
                      ↓
                 (resubmit)
Active → Matured / Sold / Rolled Over
```

## 6.2 Settlement confirmation flow

| Step | Action | Owner | Control rule |
|------|--------|-------|--------------|
| 1 | Approved deal slip routed to Back Office settlement queue | System | Only approved deals enter queue |
| 2 | Back Office reviews settlement details and generates settlement instruction | Back Office Maker | Must match approved economics and settlement account |
| 3 | Settlement instruction checked | Back Office Checker | Maker-checker mandatory |
| 4 | Payment or market settlement processed | Finance, Treasury Ops, bank signatories, or custodian | Payment release must use approved settlement instruction |
| 5 | Cash movement and external confirmation matched | Back Office | Match amount, currency, value date, counterparty, broker, custodian, documents |
| 6 | Exception created on mismatch | Back Office, Middle Office | Wrong amount, late settlement, missing confirmation, wrong account, failed settlement |
| 7 | Back Office marks settlement status | Back Office | Settled, partially settled, failed, reversed, or settled with exception |
| 8 | System updates investment register | System | **Only after settlement confirmation.** No confirmation = no active holding. |

## 6.3 Investment register update rules

| Rule | When it applies | System behaviour |
|------|-----------------|------------------|
| **Create active holding** | Only after settlement confirmed | Create official position with active status |
| **Partial settlement** | Only part of transaction settles | Active position for settled amount; exception for remaining balance |
| **Failed settlement** | Settlement does not occur | No active position. Deal status failed or cancelled |
| **Sale or disposal** | After disposal approval and settlement | Reduce or close position; compute realised gain/loss |
| **Rollover** | Maturing position reinvested | Old record marked matured/rolled over; new deal slip and new position created |
| **Manual amendment** | Controlled amendment workflow only | Require reason, approval, audit trail. Block direct overwrite |

## Build enforcement

- Deal slip status drives which actions each persona can perform — align with access matrix and journeys.
- Never skip settlement confirmation before register update.
- Partial and failed settlements must create trackable exceptions, not silent partial state.
- Rollover always creates a new deal slip + new position; never mutate settled history in place.

## 7. Minimum deal slip fields by asset class

Deal slip forms must be **dynamic by asset class**. Block submission until all mandatory fields for the selected class are populated.

| Asset class | Mandatory deal slip fields |
|-------------|---------------------------|
| **Fixed deposits and call deposits** | Counterparty, principal, rate, tenor, trade date, value date, maturity date, day count, expected interest, settlement account, rollover instruction |
| **Treasury bills and commercial papers** | Issuer, counterparty, face value, purchase price, discount rate or yield, maturity value, tenor, rating, settlement date, maturity date |
| **Bonds** | Issuer, ISIN, coupon, coupon frequency, clean price, accrued interest, dirty price, yield, settlement value, maturity date, duration, DV01 |
| **Equities** | Issuer, ticker, broker, quantity, price, fees, trade date, settlement date, settlement value, CSCS or custodian details |
| **Mutual funds** | Fund manager, fund name, units, NAV, subscription amount, redemption amount, fees, valuation date, settlement account |
| **Alternative investments** | Fund or asset name, commitment, capital call, distribution, NAV, valuation basis, approval memo, exit terms, legal documents |
